Ghana Buys 23,000 Tons of Cocoa From Farmers in First Week of Light Crop

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-06-29T10:38:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/ghana-buys-23-000-tons-of-cocoa-from-farmers-in-first-week-of-light-crop.html
Ghana  bought 23,000 metric tons of
cocoa from farmers in the week through June 16, the first week
of the light crop season, said Kwabena Asante-Poku, the deputy
chief executive officer of Ghana Cocoa Board.  Purchases from farmers for the 12-week season will probably
reach about 80,000 tons, Asante-Poku said in a phone interview
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Moses Mozart Dzawu in Accra at 
 mdzawu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
